query: Which players scored the highest individual score in AFL records? Summarize the basic information of these players.
summary: The highest individual AFL score ever recorded is held by Fred Fanning who scored 18.1 for the Melbourne Football Club against St Kilda in 1947 at Junction Oval. Gordon Coventry holds two records, having scored 17.4 for Collingwood against Fitzroy in 1930 and 16.5 for Collingwood against Hawthorn in 1929. Jason Dunstall scored 17.5 for Hawthorn against Richmond in 1992.

table.title: 1917–18 Ottawa Senators season - Schedule and results

query: What were the results of all the games that the Ottawa Senators played as the visiting team during the 1917–18 season?
summary: In 1917-18 season, Ottawa Senators have 11 games as guest team. They start their away games with a 4-11 lost to Toronto on December 22, then they have 6-3 win over Montreal Wanderers on December 26. After that, their away games had mix results, with a 5-6 lost to Montreal Canadiens on January 5, 4-9 lost to same team on January 12, and 4-5 lost to Toronto on January 16. Then Senators win two more away games, beat Canadiens 4-3 on January 23 and 3-1 on February 27, but they lost 2-8 to Toronto on February 4, 1-3 to Toronto on February 11,3-9 to Toronto on February 23 and 4-10 to Canadiens on February 16.
